In the current version there are some weaknesses which might get improved in future releases.

- Currently the HMAC to provide authenticity is weak
- Denial of service attacks are easy when using google api.
  - Login information are static so can be used to steal messages so they never get received
  - There is a limit of traffic as the app uses a free limit
- Limited amount of generated keys per offline device
- UserId exchange is limited to be secure when people meet each other
- No verification if bluetooth partner is a valid ParAnnoying User
- Hash algorithms needs to be verified
- Bluetooth and NFC can be used to communicate in both directions and Security issues like stagefright can be used to hijack the offline device
- The offline device might already have a trojan which is controlling connections without the user can do anything and is wrongly feeling safe
- When downloading the apk it might get injected with malicious code and so might be useless. This is a considered practice for governments which abuse ISPs.
The only solution is to compile open source code on your own
- There is a lack of uniqueness of online ids especially those which are used without google api
- All private data is loaded into ram. So attackers with root permissions could easily read. And performance might be an issue with long time usage.